# MCP Tool Development Guidelines

## Tool Registration
All tools must be registered in [packages/backend/src/mcp-server.ts](mdc:packages/backend/src/mcp-server.ts):

```typescript
server.registerTool(
  "tool-name",
  {
    title: "Human Readable Title",
    description: "Detailed description with examples",
    inputSchema: ToolSchema,
  },
  toolHandler
);
```

## Tool Structure Requirements
1. **Schema File** (`schema.ts`):
   - Use Zod for validation
   - Include descriptive text for each parameter
   - Use appropriate Zod types (string, number, boolean, etc.)

2. **Tool File** (`tool.ts`):
   - Export handler function with proper typing
   - Include comprehensive logging
   - Handle errors gracefully
   - Return structured responses

3. **Index Export** ([packages/backend/src/tools/index.ts](mdc:packages/backend/src/tools/index.ts)):
   - Export both schema and handler
   - Use consistent naming pattern

## Response Format
All tools must return responses in this format:
```typescript
{
  content: [
    {
      type: "text",
      text: "Response content",
    },
  ],
}
```

## Logging Standards
- Use consistent prefixes: `[tool-name] Message`
- Log input parameters (sanitized)
- Log database operations
- Log errors with full context
- Log successful operations with key metrics

## Database Integration
- Use typed collections from [packages/backend/src/db/collections/](mdc:packages/backend/src/db/collections/)
- Always validate ObjectIds before database queries
- Handle missing documents gracefully
- Update related documents when needed

## Error Handling
- Return user-friendly error messages
- Log technical details for debugging
- Update document status on failures
- Provide actionable feedback when possible
